EVA Airways signs deal with Boeing
today to buy three B777-300ER planes, according to a co.
statement.
*EVA to lease four B777-300ER planes from GE Capital Aviation
Services: statement
*Delivery between June 2014-June 2016: statement
*Cargo demand has improved “slightly” after bottoming in 1Q,
Nieh Kuo-wei, the carrier’s spokesman, says
*EVA has an option for four more B777-300ER planes: co.
President Chang Kuo-wei
*EVA to buy 3 B777-300ER aircraft for about $930m: statement to
